sql:
SELECT student_id
FROM academics
WHERE gpa > (SELECT AVG(gpa) FROM academics);

SELECT COUNT(student_id) AS Total_Students
FROM academics
WHERE gpa > 2.5 AND semester_gpa > 2.5;

SELECT AVG(T1.gpa) AS average_gpa
FROM academics T1
WHERE T1.completed_credits > 50 AND T1.gpa > (
  SELECT AVG(gpa)
  FROM academics
);

external_knowledge:
- 'alchemists' refers to students in the Chemistry department;
- 'surpassed the threshold of excellence' refers to having a GPA greater than 3.0;
- 'total weight of the academic achievements' refers to the sum of completed credits.

- "shining star" refers to the major with the best academic performance;
- "academic summit" refers to the completion of degree requirements;
- "highest average GPA" indicates the best academic performance;
- "least amount of credits remaining" indicates that students are close to completing their degree.

- "High-achieving students" refers to students with a cumulative GPA greater than 3.5 and a semester GPA greater than 3.5;
- "Significant course load" refers to students enrolled in courses with more than 5 credits;
- The results are ordered by cumulative GPA and semester GPA in descending order, indicating the top-performing students.

- "available spots" refers to the difference between the total enrollments and the sum of enrolled and waitlisted students;
- "total enrollments" includes all enrollment records, regardless of status;
- "total enrolled" and "total waitlisted" are the sums of students in these statuses across all offerings of the course.

